# Config README Sync Rule

Whenever you modify any of the following, you MUST also update `data/config/README.md`:

## Triggers → what to update in the README

| What changed | README section(s) to update |
|---|---|
| New JSON key added to any config file | Matching file's field table |
| JSON key removed or renamed | Matching file's field table |
| Override value format changed (e.g. new syntax) | `chaos_joints.json → overrides` section, value format table |
| New relational rule type added to `constraints.py` | `constraints.json → Relational rule types` — add a new subsection with schema and example |
| Existing rule type behavior changed | Update that rule's subsection |
| New config file added | Add it to the Files table and write a new section for it |
| Config file removed | Remove its entry from the Files table and its section |
| Path resolution logic changed | Update path descriptions in `runner.json` section |

## Format rules for the README

- Every rule type must have: a one-line description, a JSON schema example, and a field table or inline field notes
- Every config file section must have a minimal valid JSON example showing all top-level keys
- Field tables must include: field name, type, and description
- Do not add implementation details or Python internals — the README is for config authors, not developers
